<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="vivid-adj">vivid <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'vɪvɪd/    美 /'vɪvɪd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>(色彩) 鲜艳的；鲜明的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is wearing a vivid red coat.
她穿着一件鲜红色的外套。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(表现、描述等) 逼真的；(想象力) 丰富的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 vague </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a vivid description
生动的描述</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve got vivid memories of my happy childhood.
我对自己快乐的童年记忆犹新。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I’m not surprised that he became a writer. Even as a child he had a <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (丰富的) imagination.  （2009 天津改）<br />
A.clear<br />
B.cautious<br />
C.funny<br />
D.vivid  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. vivid  </p></div>